Subject: [PATCH] GrindrPlus: fix `withSuspendResult` intercepting wrong continuation instances.

`withSuspendResult` hooked `invokeSuspend` at the class level, causing concurrent Retrofit calls sharing the same continuation class to intercept each other's results. This led to albums showing as empty and soft-crashing when swiping, as one call's handler received another call's `kotlin.Unit` result.

- Add `thisObject()` identity check to only process the targeted continuation instance
- Remove `isResult()`  early-return guards from #232 that prevented coroutine handling entirely
- Add `isSuccess()` guards in handleGetAlbum, parseAlbumContent and fetchAlbumFromDatabase to safely skip non-Success values
- Update hookService doc comment to warn against isResult() pattern

Fixes #65, #99. Supersedes #232.
